WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.536
Management is etiology-guided.

00:00:01.536 --> 00:00:04.609
For all patients, activity restriction for

00:00:04.609 --> 00:00:07.682
3 to 6 months is recommended

00:00:07.682 --> 00:00:09.730
to reduce arrhythmia risk.

00:00:09.730 --> 00:00:12.803
Guideline-directed medical therapy — ACE inhibitors,

00:00:12.803 --> 00:00:15.876
beta-blockers, diuretics — is the cornerstone

00:00:15.876 --> 00:00:17.924
for heart failure presentations.

00:00:17.924 --> 00:00:20.997
Immunosuppression with IV glucocorticoids is indicated

00:00:20.997 --> 00:00:24.070
for giant cell, eosinophilic, sarcoid, and

00:00:24.070 --> 00:00:25.094
ICI-associated myocarditis.

00:00:25.094 --> 00:00:28.167
Mechanical circulatory support bridges fulminant cases.

00:00:28.167 --> 00:00:31.239
Cardiac transplantation remains the definitive therapy

00:00:31.239 --> 00:00:33.800
for refractory giant cell myocarditis.
